rocketride-bench — what is RocketRide vs. what is this repo
===========================================================

The SYSTEM UNDER TEST is the genuine, unmodified RocketRide product:

  * Engine (C++ runtime) ..... official release `rocketride-server-v3.2.1-<platform>`
                               from github.com/rocketride-org/rocketride-server
                               (or the public ghcr.io/rocketride-org/rocketride-engine image)
  * EAAS server ............. the bundle's `ai/eaas.py` on ws://localhost:5565
  * SDK / client ............ the published `rocketride` PyPI package (v1.2.0)
  * Tracer .................. the engine's native tracer (apaevt_flow / apaevt_status_update)
  * Provider nodes + catalog  the engine's shipped nodes + the generated .rocketride catalog

This repo NEVER reimplements engine behavior — it only DRIVES and MEASURES the real product.

The ONLY code we add is measurement scaffolding:

  * harness/ .............. drives the SDK, captures the tracer to JSONL, measures CPU/RSS
  * nodes/workload/ ..... a synthetic benchmark-only node (CPU/sleep/HTTP/crash modes). It is
                            NOT part of RocketRide and is safe to delete; it runs INSIDE the real
                            engine exactly as any user-authored node would.
  * harness/lc_baselines.py + nodes/workload/IInstance.py — the deterministic fixed-latency model
                            (`time.sleep`) and `busy()` CPU loop, AST-identical on BOTH the RocketRide node
                            and the LangChain function side, so numbers reflect the framework, not API variance.

